    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>את אחי אנוכי מבקש ואחר ד"ש הטוב באתי לבקש לדבר אל ידידי</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">L. Phillips</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>203 Broome St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Feb 5</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Friday, the 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Shevat</date>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>1863</date>, <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
            <p>
                <add>לשלוח לי את האחד אשר שמעתי מידידי והוא אמר לו לטובה</add>
            </p>
            <p>Peace and goodness forever. I seek my<lb/> brethren, and with a greeting of peace, I
                come to<lb/> speak to my friend, <persName>Rabbi Eliezer
                    <sic>Lesser</sic></persName>, editor,<lb/> of the “Occident,” to send me one
                copy, for I<lb/> have heard from my friend <persName>Leffenherz</persName>, who was in<lb/>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, that you mention me for good with re-<lb/>gard
                to the matter about which I argued with<lb/> the Chazan <persName>Isaacs</persName>
                which you have no doubt<lb/> noticed in The Israelite, and which completely
                re-<lb/>futed him, because he was acquainted with me<lb/> for twenty-five years.
                Why, then, did you not<lb/> ask me? Why did you do this? Perhaps I could<lb/> have
                found a reply of my own, to prove that<lb/> I had done right. To make it brief,
                because the<lb/> letter must be on its way, I beg of <persName>Mr. Eliezar<lb/>
                    <sic>Lesser</sic></persName>, to send to me the said copy of the<lb/> Occident
                to my address, and I shall reim<lb/>burse you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your servant, ready to<lb/> serve you, with greetings to your wife
                and<lb/> children from me and my household,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">L. Phillips</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>203 Broome St.</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
